  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\nBefore if you dismiss \"Error connecting to mailserver\" popup (by tapping \"Cancel\") - you can see popup again on tapping banner in the header (\"Tap to reconnect\")\nCurrently, popup appears again in several seconds, so can't dismiss it\n\n#### Expected behavior\nbutton \"Cancel\" closes popup (con see it again if tap on \"Tap to reconnect\" in case of unsuccessful connection)\n\n#### Actual behavior\npoup reappears\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status\n- Go to Profile > Sync settings > Mailserver\n- Turn off automatic selection\n- Add mailserver, that matches required format, but in fact invalid (i.e. enode://ee2b53b0ace9692167a510515bca3025695dbf0e1a68e1dff9716da620efb195f05a5b9e873fb9b75ac85de801106c565b8e2b6c5f0d93b8759d1578bfcaf03e:password@105.197.238.155:553 )\n- Connect to it\n- In \"Error connecting to mailserver\" tap \"Cancel\"\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: nightly 21/02/2020\n- Operating System: Android, iOS",
